# ASP.NET Identity Best Practices

This document outlines the best practices for implementing authentication and authorization using ASP.NET Identity in this project.

- Use ASP.NET Identity for user management, authentication, and authorization
- Implement role-based authorization to control access to resources
- Use JWT tokens for stateless authentication in API scenarios
- Enable two-factor authentication for enhanced security

